  "body": "This is something I ran into when working on handling sync setting messages (#5201).\r\n\r\nIn `CurrencyStore` we have a `currentCurrency` property that represents the current default currency. When that property changes, we have a `*Changed` handler that ensures the currency model for the language & currency view is updated accordingly.\r\n\r\nHere's what the handler looks like:\r\n\r\n```qml\r\n    onCurrentCurrencyChanged: { \r\n      updateCurrenciesModel()\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd `updateCurrenciesModel` looks like this:\r\n\r\n```qml\r\n    function updateCurrenciesModel() {\r\n        var isSelected = false\r\n        for(var i = 0; i < currenciesModel.count; i++) {\r\n            if(root.currentCurrency === root.currenciesModel.get(i).key) {\r\n              isSelected = true\r\n                root.currenciesModel.get(i).selected = true\r\n            }\r\n            else {\r\n                root.currenciesModel.get(i).selected = false\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        // Set default:\r\n        if(!isSelected)\r\n            root.currenciesModel.get(0).selected = true\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I was working on #5201 I got a signal from a service that the currency has changed (via sync), which then triggered a changes in the wallet section's `currentCurrency`, which then in turn is a change in `CurrencyStore.currentyCurrency`, which will ultimately trigger the `onCurrentCurrencyChanged` handler.\r\n\r\nThis is great, because we want the UI to update when there's such a change coming from the service.\r\n\r\nNow the sad through is that we realized, even though the correct model is updated and set to `selected = true`, the currency selector in the settings view for languages and currency is **not** updated correctly.\r\n\r\nThis can be easily reproduced by adding the following snippet to the `LanguageView.qml`:\r\n\r\n```qml\r\n        StatusButton {\r\n          text: \"Test\"\r\n          onClicked: {\r\n              root.currencyStore.currentCurrency = \"eur\"\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\n^ Clicking this button will trigger the change in the currency, which will cause the currency model to update, however the update is not reflected in the view for some reason.\r\n\r\n@noeliaSD has looked into this as well.\r\n\r\n",
