    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> * Also the manual model filtering transfer is a maintenance burden. The usual C++ way is to build a proxy model, not sure if this can be easily done in NIM, but it is a more efficient way. Otherwise every change you do in the model you have to propagate it to delegates, as mentioned above\r\n\r\nExactly! Imperative model building/filtering is [asking for trouble](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/5823#discussion_r885659791). I will take a look at the possibility to integrate `QSortFilterProxyModel` based utilities into StatusQ: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/6509",
