    "body": "If I have to guess I would say this must be an issue similar to [this](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/5823#discussion_r885659791). Manually built filtered model in `StatusListPicker` is not able to detect source model property changes :man_shrugging: \r\n\r\nThe quick and dirty solution would be :cry: : \r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/ui/app/AppLayouts/Profile/views/LanguageView.qml b/ui/app/AppLayouts/Profile/views/LanguageView.qml\r\nindex 847611e2f..859fa9554 100644\r\n--- a/ui/app/AppLayouts/Profile/views/LanguageView.qml\r\n+++ b/ui/app/AppLayouts/Profile/views/LanguageView.qml\r\n@@ -74,6 +74,15 @@ SettingsContentBase {\r\n                 placeholderSearchText: qsTr(\"Search Currencies\")\r\n                 maxPickerHeight: 350\r\n \r\n+                Conections {\r\n+                    target: root.currencyStore\r\n+                    onCurrentCurrencyChanged: {\r\n+                        // Force rebuild filter model in StatusListPicker\r\n+                        currencyPicker.inputList = null\r\n+                        currencyPicker.inputList = Qt.binding(() => root.currencyStore.currenciesModel)\r\n+                    }\r\n+                }\r\n+\r\n                 onItemPickerChanged: {\r\n                     if(selected) {\r\n                         currencyPicker.newKey = key\r\n```\r\n**(haven't tested it)**",
